   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from itertools import combinations\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_iris\n",
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "id": "41101e45-05bb-431a-a7a4-79afa6cef433",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "clf = DecisionTreeClassifier().fit(X, y)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "142abbed-ae56-413b-a056-3a8eb04968a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plot_colors = \"ryb\"\n",
    "plot_step = 0.02 "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "id": "5b494ddc-1cfd-491e-81e9-09c5fc2dd5ea",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x800 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pairs = combinations(range(X.shape[1]), 2)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8)) \n",
    "for i, (pair_1, pair_2) in enumerate(pairs):\n",
    "    X_pair = X[:, [pair_1, pair_2]]\n",
    "    clf.fit(X_pair, y)\n",
    "    x_min, x_max = X_pair[:, 0].min() - 1, X_pair[:, 0].max() + 1\n",
    "    y_min, y_max = X_pair[:, 1].min() - 1, X_pair[:, 1].max() + 1\n",
    "    xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, plot_step),np.arange(y_min, y_max, plot_step))\n",
    "    Z = clf.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])\n",
    "    Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)\n",
    "    plt.subplot(2, 3, i + 1)\n",
    "    plt.contourf(xx, yy, Z, cmap=plt.cm.RdYlBu)\n",
    "    plt.scatter(X_pair[:, 0], X_pair[:, 1], c=y, edgecolor='k', cmap=plt.cm.RdYlBu)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(iris.feature_names[pair_1])\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(iris.feature_names[pair_2])\n",
    "plt.suptitle(\"Decision surface of decision trees trained on pairs of features\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
